other_tests.findings: Mild prominence of the extrahepatic biliary tree with maximum diameter of 13 mm. No upstream dilatation of the intrahepatic bile ducts. The common bile duct tapers without filling defect or extrinsic mass effect. Contour of the bile ducts is smooth, without areas of stenosis, irregularity or thickening. Anomalous low insertion of the right posterior bile duct into the common hepatic duct. Normal liver size and contour, with normal parenchymal signal. No focal hepatic lesion identified. Unremarkable pancreas, pancreatic duct, spleen, right kidney, and adrenal glands. A 1.5 cm hemorrhagic cyst in the left mid kidney. No lymphadenopathy or ascites. Mild atelectatic changes noted at each lung base.
